An anonymous reader writes "An editor from Wired writes on his blog that
[0]Wikipedia sucks for science stories ‚Äî not because they are inaccurate,
but because of what he calls the 'tragedy of the uncommon': Too many
experts writing about subjects in ways that no non-expert can understand.
Would this be the dumbing-down of Wikipedia ‚Äî or would it be a better
resource for everyone?"

